modules.description: This module defines error types and operations for handling type comparison errors. It includes a variant type `t` for representing specific error cases, such as `Ids_not_equal`, and provides functions to check equality between error values and to format them for display. It is used when comparing type identifiers to capture and report mismatches with detailed error messages.

This module creates and compares type identifiers with labels, producing equality proofs or detailed errors when they differ. It works with a polymorphic type `t` and supports operations to retrieve labels, check equality, and handle type mismatches using a dedicated error variant. Concrete use cases include ensuring type consistency in data structures like maps or during type-checking passes in compilers.
